How the financial rules of football will affect the move of Neymar to Paris
The rules, aimed at preventing unlimited spending by European football clubs, will not prevent the world record transfer of Neymar from the Spanish “Barcelona” to the French “Paris Saint-Germain”.
Any consequences can come further down the chain, for Paris Saint-Germain by UEFA, the governing body that controls European football, in whose power to prohibit teams from participating in the prestigious Champions League tournament.
From the rules of financial fair play introduced by UEFA in 2011, it follows that PSG will eventually have to show that the transfer of Neymar was financed without major losses.
