In Ukraine proposed to send Russians to prison for illegal border crossing
In the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine registered a draft law according to which in the republic may appear a criminal penalty for Russians for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, the document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament provides for a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens trying to illegally enter the country.
It is noted that for a repeated offense or an act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the offender was detained at the border with a weapon, the time of detention for him will increase to eight years.
Earlier it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians who tried to enter Russia outside the established checkpoints.
