In Moscow, a policeman wounded a man in the leg, defending himself from an attack
A police officer shot a member of the fight in Moscow in the leg after he attacked him with a piece of glass in his hand.
On August 3, in the evening, the police department of the OMVD of Russia in the Yakimanka district received a report of a fight on Mytnaya Street, 46.
"The arrived police squad stopped the offense and separated the participants of the conflict," RIA Novosti reported with reference to the press service of the capital's Interior Ministry.
According to the police, when one of the participants of the conflict attacked an employee of the Ministry of Internal Affairs with a piece of glass, the policeman several times warned the man about the use of weapons and made a warning shot.
This did not stop the bully, after which a law enforcement officer shot the man in the leg.
The injured man needed hospitalization.
